  "description": [
    "TEN YEARS OF PROGRESS IN CIVIL RIGHTS The beginning of a new year is customarily a time for a sumrhing up of the past as well as an estimate of the future And among the many reviews of the nations development that have been appearing during this seasonal stocktaking one that should be of particular interest both at home and abroad deeds with civil rights Published in pamphlet form by the American Jewish Committeea pri vatelyfinanced organization devoted to socied studies and community bet termentthis report covers the past ten years It is entitled The People Take the Lead and is especially note worthy because it presents summa tions of various aspects of civil rights progress by leaders in their respective fields me wore oi me reaerai govern ment in combating racial discrimina tion in employment is described by Vice President Richard M Nixon Noting that the Federal Government is the largest employer in the coun tryit has more than five million people on its payroll both civilian and militaryMr Nixon writes With little fuss and fanfare the Federal Government has been sweep ing the cobwebs of discrimination out of its own offices Americans are now assured that Government serv"
